\tan\theta=\frac ab
\frac{\sin\theta}a=\frac{\cos\theta}b=\pm\sqrt{\frac{\sin^2\theta+\cos^2\theta}{a^2+b^2}}=\pm\frac1{\sqrt{a^2+b^2}}
b=1,
\tan\theta=a,\frac{\sin\theta}a=\frac{\cos\theta}1=\pm\frac1{\sqrt{a^2+1}}
